<plot>Flying was all the rage in 1929, two years after Charles Lindbergh soloed across the Atlantic, and when Bill Bibichkow and Sam Goldenberg, high school students from a Chicago slum, opened the Comet Model Airplane &amp; Supply Co. Initial capital: $5. See how the boys turned a few sticks of balsa wood, music wire, tissue and glue into a million dollar business, much to the delight of model builders across America.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?549660</url></doc>
